-- Chinese bank BoCom H1 profit up 5.6 pct, meets estimates
-- 
-- Thu Aug 21, 2014 04:57AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG/SHANGHAI, Aug 21 (Reuters) - China's Bank of Communications Co Ltd <601328.SS> <3328.HK>, the country's fifth-largest listed bank, reported a 5.6 percent rise in first half net profit, in line with forecasts, as interest income remained steady.

BoCom on Thursday posted net profit of 36.77 billion yuan($5.98 billion) for the January-June period. A Reuters poll of analysts had forecast net income of 36.9 billion yuan for the first half. The first-half figure implies a net profit of 18.08 billion yuan in the second quarter, up 5.6 percent from the same year ago period.